==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Roup
<hw>Roup</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i. & t.</pos> <ety>[Cf. AS. hr<?/pan
to cry out, G. <ets>rufen</ets>, Goth. <ets>hr<?/pian</ets>. Cf.
<er>Roop</er>.]</ety> <def>To cry or shout; hence, to sell by
auction.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Jamieson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roup</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Roup
<hw>Roup</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An outcry; hence, a sale
of gods by auction.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>
<rj><au>Jamieson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To <qex>roup</qex>, that is, the sale of his crops, was over.</q>
<rj><qau>J. C. Shairp.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A disease in poultry. See <er>Pip</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rousant</ent>⟦br⟧
